Troubleshooting Common Issues
Script Execution Problems
Issue: Permission denied when running scripts Solution:

chmod +x script_name.sh
Issue: Script can't find directories Solution: Check paths and create missing directories:

mkdir -p ~/test_data ~/backups ~/scheduled_backups
Cron Job Issues
Issue: Cron jobs not executing Solution:

Check cron service: systemctl status cron
Verify cron syntax using online cron validators
Use absolute paths in cron jobs
Issue: Scripts work manually but fail in cron Solution: Add full PATH to scripts:

PATH=/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin
Log File Problems
Issue: Cannot write to log files Solution: Check permissions and create log files manually:

touch ~/backup_log.txt ~/cron_backup.log
chmod 644 ~/backup_log.txt ~/cron_backup.log
